  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Overview&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The following steps are performed in this tool mentor:&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a href=&quot;#Distribute%20Subsystem%20behavior&quot;>Distribute Subsystem Behavior to Subsystem Elements&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a href=&quot;#Document%20Subsystem%20Elements&quot;>Document Subsystem Elements&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a href=&quot;#Describe%20Subsystem%20Dependencies&quot;>Describe Subsystem Dependencies&lt;/a>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;a href=&quot;#MoreInfo&quot;>Additional Tool Information&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Distribute Subsystem behavior&quot; name=&quot;Distribute Subsystem behavior&quot;>Distribute Subsystem Behavior to Subsystem&#xD;
    Elements&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Classes and other subsystems are added within the subsystem to realize the subsystem interfaces.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The collaborations of model elements within the subsystem must be documented using sequence diagrams that show how the&#xD;
    subsystem behavior is realized. Each operation on an interface that is realized by the subsystem must have one or more&#xD;
    documented sequence diagrams. This diagram, which is owned by the subsystem, is used to design the internal behavior of&#xD;
    the subsystem.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create class diagrams as needed. See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot;&#xD;
        src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Creating and Modifying Class Diagrams&lt;/i> .&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Add subsystems and classes. See &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../core.base_rup/tasks/identify_design_elements_E884AB82.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{97D7343A-6993-4AB7-8F86-4DAC8C9075C8}&quot;>Identify Design Elements&lt;/a> for guidance on adding new subsystems&#xD;
        and classes.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Document how each interface operation is realized, as follows:&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li style=&quot;list-style: none&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Add a collaboration instance for each interface operation. Name it after the operation. In the Model&#xD;
                Explorer, right-click the subsystem and then click &lt;b>Add UML&lt;/b> &lt;b>&amp;gt; Collaboration&lt;/b>. &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Create an interaction with the same name. In the Model Explorer, right-click the collaboration and then&#xD;
                click &lt;b>Add Diagram &amp;gt; Sequence Diagram&lt;/b>. See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot;&#xD;
                src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Sequence Diagrams&lt;/i> .&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Drag and drop classes and interfaces onto the diagram to create objects for interaction.&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Add messages or stimuli between objects. See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot;&#xD;
                src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Sequence Diagrams&lt;/i>.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                Assign operations to messages. See &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot;&#xD;
                src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Sequence Diagrams&lt;/i>. &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For more information, refer to the following topics in the online Help:&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Modeling Static&#xD;
        Structure&amp;nbsp;by Using&amp;nbsp;Class Diagrams&lt;/i>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Sequence&#xD;
        Diagrams&lt;/i>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Document Subsystem Elements&quot; name=&quot;Document Subsystem Elements&quot;>Document Subsystem Elements&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Refer to &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Documenting&#xD;
    Model Elements&lt;/i> in the online Help.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;Describe Subsystem Dependencies&quot; name=&quot;Describe Subsystem Dependencies&quot;>Describe Subsystem Dependencies&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    When an element contained in a subsystem uses some behavior of an element contained in another subsystem, a dependency&#xD;
    is created between the enclosing subsystems. To improve reuse and reduce maintenance dependencies, express this&#xD;
    situation in terms of a dependency on a particular interface of the subsystem, not upon the subsystem itself nor upon&#xD;
    the element contained in the subsystem.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Refer to &lt;img height=&quot;16&quot; alt=&quot;help book icon&quot; src=&quot;../../../core.base_rup/resources/helpbook.gif&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; />&lt;i>Dependency&#xD;
    Relationships&lt;/i> in the online Help.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    &lt;a id=&quot;MoreInfo&quot; name=&quot;MoreInfo&quot;>Additional Tool Information&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
